From: Blakestream-GaintB <sid@blakestream.local>
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] driver-baikalu: skip disabled miners in baikal_update_work

The factory cod3gen/sgminer-baikal binary has a fatal deadlock when any
single ASC is disabled via the api.c:ascdisable() command:

  - api.c:ascdisable() sets cgpu->deven = DEV_DISABLED but doesn't tell
    the driver
  - On the next block change, baikal_update_work() iterates ALL miners
    (not just enabled ones) and pushes new work to each via baikal_send_work
  - The disabled miner's work queue fills up because the disabled mining
    thread isn't processing it
  - Eventually baikal_send_work returns false and triggers baikal_cleanup
    which sets deven=DEV_DISABLED for the WHOLE device (all miners)
  - Result: all 3 boards stop mining when any one is ascdisable'd

This patch fixes part 1: skip miners that are administratively disabled
when iterating in baikal_update_work().
---
 driver-baikalu.c | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/driver-baikalu.c b/driver-baikalu.c
--- a/driver-baikalu.c
+++ b/driver-baikalu.c
@@ -880,6 +880,17 @@ static void baikal_update_work(struct cgpu_info *baikal)

         for (i = 0; i < info->miner_count; i++) {
             miner = &info->miners[i];
+
+            /* Skip miners that have been administratively disabled (e.g.
+             * via the API ascdisable command). Pushing new work to them
+             * fills their FIFO and eventually causes baikal_send_work to
+             * fail, which the existing recovery path treats as a fatal
+             * device error - shutting down ALL miners on the device. */
+            {
+                struct thr_info *t = mining_thr[miner->thr_id];
+                if (t && t->cgpu && t->cgpu->deven == DEV_DISABLED)
+                    continue;
+            }
 #if BAIKAL_CHECK_STALE
             /* set work stale */
             mutex_lock(baikal->mutex);
